Description: Eliminate glMapBuffer pipeline stalls (stuttering fix)
 glMapBuffer forces the CPU to wait until the GPU has finished reading the
 buffer before it can be mapped.  With 6 consecutive map/unmap cycles on the
 same BigCube VBO per frame, plus one GL_READ_WRITE map on the 774 KB point
 cloud percentages buffer, the main loop stalled up to 7 times every frame —
 enough to push render time well past the 16.6 ms vsync window and cause
 visible stuttering.
 .
 The fix uses buffer orphaning: glBufferData(target, size, NULL, hint) tells
 the driver to allocate a fresh backing store for the buffer object.  The GPU
 keeps the previous backing store for any in-flight draw calls while the CPU
 writes to the new one without any synchronisation stall.  A single
 glBufferSubData then uploads the new data.
 .
 bigcube.c / bigcube.h:
   updateBigCube() no longer makes any OpenGL call; it only updates the
   already-maintained CPU array bc->vertices.  A new flushBigCube() performs
   the orphan + upload in one GL call pair.
 .
 antagonism.c:
   Call flushBigCube() once after the 6 updateBigCube() calls so the whole
   VBO is uploaded in a single transfer instead of 6 separate map/unmap pairs.
 .
 pointcloud.c:
   updatePC() now computes into the CPU array pc.percentages (which was
   already malloc'd and kept alive), then orphans and uploads.  Removes the
   GL_READ_WRITE flag which forced an unnecessary 774 KB readback from GPU
   memory on every frame.
